WEBVTT

00:32.500 --> 00:35.833
<i> Mr. Spenser, are you prepared</i>
<i>to tell the court, in your own words,</i>

00:35.916 --> 00:38.000
<i>what happened on the afternoon</i>
<i>of March 20th?</i>

00:38.083 --> 00:39.916
<i>Yes, Your Honor.</i>

00:40.000 --> 00:41.625
<i>Please proceed.</i>

00:41.708 --> 00:45.416
<i> I had my partner drive me</i>
<i>to the home of Captain John Boylan.</i>

00:45.500 --> 00:46.791
<i>Your commanding officer?</i>

00:47.416 --> 00:48.541
<i>That's right.</i>

00:49.083 --> 00:50.125
<i>I had prior reason to believe</i>

00:50.208 --> 00:51.833
<i>that Captain Boylan</i>
<i>was intentionally burying</i>

00:51.916 --> 00:53.458
<i>the murder investigation</i>
<i>of Gloria Weisnewski--</i>

00:53.541 --> 00:56.541
<i>Mr. Spenser,</i>
<i>please focus on the events that transpired</i>

00:56.625 --> 00:58.500
<i>-on the afternoon of March 20th.</i>

01:00.666 --> 01:02.791
<i>I confronted</i>
<i>Captain Boylan in his home</i>

01:02.875 --> 01:05.541
<i>and attempted to question him</i>
<i>about the investigation.</i>

01:06.916 --> 01:08.708
The hell are you doing here?

01:09.416 --> 01:10.916
<i>And the ensuing argument...</i>

01:11.000 --> 01:12.541
Can't wait outside
the front door?

01:12.625 --> 01:15.500
<i>I mean,</i>
<i>everybody knows what happened.</i>

01:16.833 --> 01:18.166
Get out of our house!

01:18.250 --> 01:20.375
Hey! Get out of here.
Get the fuck out of our house--

01:21.916 --> 01:25.875
<i>At all times, I knew that these</i>
<i>actions were in violation of the law</i>

01:25.958 --> 01:30.375
<i>and the code of conduct that I swore</i>
<i>to obey as a Boston police officer.</i>

01:30.458 --> 01:33.166
<i>So, it is my understanding</i>
<i>that you are pleading guilty</i>

01:33.250 --> 01:35.500
<i>to the charge of disturbing the peace?</i>

01:35.583 --> 01:36.583
<i>Yes, Your Honor.</i>

01:37.166 --> 01:40.208
<i>How do you plead on the count</i>
<i>of harassment in the first degree?</i>

01:40.291 --> 01:41.833
- Get off him!
- <i>Guilty.</i>

01:41.916 --> 01:45.791
<i>And how do you plead on the count</i>
<i>of aggravated assault of a police officer?</i>

01:45.875 --> 01:46.750
<i>Guilty.</i>

01:46.833 --> 01:48.333
<i>Before I sentence you,</i>

01:48.416 --> 01:50.666
<i>is there anything further</i>
<i>that you would like to add?</i>

01:51.208 --> 01:53.791
<i>Yes.</i>
<i>The son of a bitch deserved it.</i>

02:31.166 --> 02:32.375
What do you say, Spense?

02:32.958 --> 02:34.791
-Hey, Squeeb.

02:34.875 --> 02:36.958
Hey, new little fun fact for you.

02:37.041 --> 02:40.208
You know, Saguaro cactus
lives for over 150 years?

02:40.291 --> 02:41.541
Now, you cut one down in Arizona,

02:41.625 --> 02:43.250
you can do a year in prison. Imagine that?

02:44.375 --> 02:45.791
Shit.

02:45.875 --> 02:47.625
I know guys that rob people in here

02:47.708 --> 02:49.375
-doin' less time than that.
- Right?

02:50.791 --> 02:52.125
How does it feel gettin' out?

02:52.208 --> 02:54.708
I haven't slept in a few nights.
But other than that...

02:54.791 --> 02:57.208
How you doin', Squeeb? How you feelin'?

02:58.250 --> 02:59.791
I feel like a lifer.

02:59.875 --> 03:01.958
You know, a lot of guys feel that way.

03:02.583 --> 03:03.750
But you're different.

03:03.833 --> 03:06.250
How many cops get to do
their time in gen pop?

03:08.000 --> 03:09.250
Zero.

03:10.166 --> 03:11.541
I can't think of one.

03:12.375 --> 03:16.333
But, I mean, that's probably why
you're so popular in here.

03:16.416 --> 03:19.250
I'm popular? Wow, I had no idea.

03:20.208 --> 03:21.625
What're you gonna do
when you get out?

03:22.666 --> 03:24.208
Back in the real world?

03:24.291 --> 03:26.458
Yeah. Go to Fenway Park,

03:26.541 --> 03:29.583
you know, get a big-ass, juicy rib eye.

03:29.666 --> 03:30.916
You got a girl, right?

03:31.000 --> 03:33.041
I got a girl. Her name is Pearl.

03:33.125 --> 03:35.750
Yeah, I'm probably just gonna
lay down in my bed

03:35.833 --> 03:37.083
and let her lick me all over.

03:38.041 --> 03:41.708
Pearl. Sounds like an old lady's name, no?

03:42.291 --> 03:45.666
You know, she's a little older.
She makes up for it in loyalty.

03:49.416 --> 03:50.791
'Sup, bookworm?

03:51.416 --> 03:52.375
Not much.

03:53.250 --> 03:55.250
How's Aryan Nation treatin' everybody?

03:55.333 --> 03:57.500
State of the Union still strong?

04:00.166 --> 04:04.541
You know, we just wanna
let you know how important it is

04:04.625 --> 04:06.916
that you're gettin' out of Boston
and never comin' back,

04:07.000 --> 04:10.041
drivin' a truck
or doin' whatever the hell you're doin'.

04:10.125 --> 04:13.333
Yeah, we have a little, uh,
goin' away message for you.

04:13.416 --> 04:14.625
For me?

04:15.416 --> 04:17.833
Well, can't be from the guys in here.

04:17.916 --> 04:19.000
They like me, right?

04:20.041 --> 04:21.833
So, who's sending the message?

04:25.333 --> 04:27.083
Fuck 'em up, Spenser.

04:40.500 --> 04:43.458
<i>♪ It's been such a long time ♪</i>

04:44.791 --> 04:45.791
All right, come on.

04:49.250 --> 04:50.583
Did you just kick me, bro?

04:51.166 --> 04:52.458
Fuck!

04:53.208 --> 04:54.958
Get the fuck outta Boston!

04:55.708 --> 04:56.875
Why you gotta kick me, bro?

05:03.833 --> 05:04.833
Who sent the message?

05:04.916 --> 05:08.541
<i>♪ I've got to keep on</i>
<i>Chasin' a dream, yeah ♪</i>

05:08.625 --> 05:11.500
<i>♪ I've gotta be on my way ♪</i>

05:11.583 --> 05:12.958
Come on, man.

05:13.500 --> 05:15.000
All right, all right, hold on!

05:16.708 --> 05:18.125
Spense.

05:19.291 --> 05:20.166
Shit.

05:20.916 --> 05:22.166
Got ya.

05:25.375 --> 05:27.791
You're lucky it was self-defense, Spenser.

05:29.416 --> 05:32.125
<i>♪ Well, I'm takin' my time</i>
<i>I'm just movin' on ♪</i>

05:32.208 --> 05:33.500
Put your hand through.

05:34.458 --> 05:36.958
Your fingerprints are
the only unique thing about you, shitbag.

05:37.041 --> 05:39.916
Seriously? You said that five years ago
when I got here.

05:40.000 --> 05:41.416
Why don't you get some new material?

05:42.208 --> 05:44.291
-I'll see you in about a month or less.
-Have a nice day.

05:48.041 --> 05:51.041
Hey, you wanna do me a favor
when you start that truck driving class?

05:51.125 --> 05:53.291
Tell my Aunt Betty I said,
"Go fuck your sister."

05:53.875 --> 05:55.833
You got a very weird family,
don't you, Lenny?

05:55.916 --> 06:00.666
<i>♪ Well, I'm takin' my time</i>
<i>I'm just movin' along ♪</i>

06:14.083 --> 06:17.250
Hey! You made it.

06:19.541 --> 06:21.375
-Nice out here, huh?

06:21.458 --> 06:23.041
Take a minute, enjoy it.

06:24.083 --> 06:25.833
Try and stay on this side for a while.

06:27.166 --> 06:30.125
Wow. Riviera hasn't aged a day.
You gonna let me drive?

06:30.208 --> 06:31.125
You remember how?

06:33.875 --> 06:35.708
Oh, shit! Get in the car! Hurry up!

06:35.791 --> 06:37.416
-Why? What's up? Why?
-Come on, I don't want her to see me.

06:37.500 --> 06:39.416
Hurry up! Come on, let's go!

06:40.750 --> 06:43.250
What are you doing?
She drove all this way to see you.

06:44.250 --> 06:45.791
Five years in prison?

06:46.500 --> 06:47.666
- Hey!

06:48.541 --> 06:53.125
Why can't you just stay out of
other people's businesses, huh?

06:53.208 --> 06:54.666
How do you like that?

06:54.750 --> 06:55.916
I love you!

06:57.125 --> 06:58.791
I love you so fuckin' much!

06:59.625 --> 07:00.541
Shit.

07:01.750 --> 07:02.958
Can't park there, ma'am.

07:03.041 --> 07:04.208
Get down!

07:04.291 --> 07:05.708
- Oh, the other side.
-What are we doin'? You--

07:05.791 --> 07:08.041
Shut up! I'm not ready to see her yet.

07:09.166 --> 07:10.916
You know, she came
all this way to see you.

07:11.000 --> 07:12.875
Henry, I'm just not ready.

07:12.958 --> 07:16.416
Heart made of granite 'cause
I find out from someone at the car wash

07:16.500 --> 07:17.708
that he got out of prison today?

07:17.791 --> 07:18.958
-Ma'am, I can't help you with that.
-No?

07:19.041 --> 07:20.583
You really gotta move your car.

07:20.666 --> 07:22.416
All right, Shawshank.
I'll move my fuckin' car.

07:22.500 --> 07:23.375
Fuck!

07:25.291 --> 07:26.416
I'm gonna kill him.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.708
<i>♪ Your love, your love ♪</i>

07:44.416 --> 07:46.000
<i>♪ Supernatural thing ♪</i>

07:50.208 --> 07:51.416
<i>♪ When we touch ♪</i>

07:52.458 --> 07:57.250
<i>♪ Give me such a funny feeling</i>
<i>In my brain ♪</i>

07:57.750 --> 07:58.875
<i>♪ Oh, babe ♪</i>

08:00.458 --> 08:01.750
<i>♪ Your love ♪</i>

08:01.833 --> 08:05.000
<i>♪ Your love, your love ♪</i>

08:05.083 --> 08:06.916
<i>♪ Supernatural thing ♪</i>

08:07.000 --> 08:09.208
<i>-♪ Supernatural ♪</i>
<i>-♪ Oh, babe ♪</i>

08:09.291 --> 08:10.791
<i>♪ Supernatural ♪</i>

08:10.875 --> 08:12.666
<i>♪ Your love, your love ♪</i>

08:12.750 --> 08:14.875
<i>♪ Your love, your love ♪</i>

08:19.625 --> 08:23.333
Back in the day, my old man
bought this place for 8,000 bucks.

08:24.083 --> 08:28.541
Now it's worth $1,500,000 per floor.

08:28.625 --> 08:31.000
Sell it, live the dream.
Come to Arizona with me.

08:31.083 --> 08:34.125
Nah.
My dream is to die in my bed, right here.

08:34.208 --> 08:35.291
- Spenser!

08:37.583 --> 08:38.833
What's up, Driscoll?

08:38.916 --> 08:41.375
- Spenser. Come here.
-What's up?

08:44.541 --> 08:47.041
I'm sorry I couldn't visit you
more at Walpole, brother.

08:47.125 --> 08:48.791
Look, I'm glad you came up.

08:48.875 --> 08:50.875
And I really appreciate
you sendin' me the books. It's all good.

08:50.958 --> 08:52.125
I brought you a gift.

08:52.958 --> 08:55.375
-Donuts?
-I wanna keep you on your toes.

08:55.458 --> 08:57.083
-Hey.

08:58.291 --> 08:59.916
Impressive how you did your time.

09:00.625 --> 09:01.916
As a former police officer,

09:02.000 --> 09:04.041
I was very, very popular in there.
That's for sure.

09:04.958 --> 09:08.583
Man. So, what's next?
That's the big question.

09:08.666 --> 09:11.166
Look, I'm gettin outta here, you know?

09:11.250 --> 09:13.708
There ain't shit for me here.
I'm gonna drive a semi, you know?

09:13.791 --> 09:15.416
Look at sunsets. Shit like that.

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
Ah, maybe it's for the best.

09:18.083 --> 09:20.708
There's still a lot of cops around here
who'd love to put a mark on you.

09:20.791 --> 09:23.208
Well, I get in a hassle,
I know who to call.

09:23.291 --> 09:24.583
That's fuckin' right.

09:25.083 --> 09:27.916
All right, man, welcome home, brother.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.583
I love you. Nice to see you, brother.

09:31.208 --> 09:33.166
How you doin' today, Mr. Cimoli?

09:34.000 --> 09:35.083
I'm good.

09:37.958 --> 09:40.250
-Say hi to Irene and the boys.
-You got it.

09:41.666 --> 09:43.291
Let's go see your girlfriend.

09:44.916 --> 09:45.958
Pearl.

09:46.583 --> 09:49.333
Pearly, baby. Hey.

09:50.041 --> 09:50.916
Pearly.

09:52.166 --> 09:54.458
Henry, she won't even look at me.

09:54.541 --> 09:55.625
She gave me the cold shoulder.

09:55.708 --> 09:59.250
Baby, I'm sorry that I was gone.
I know five years is way too long.

09:59.958 --> 10:01.791
Thirty-five years from her perspective.

10:01.875 --> 10:03.250
No more cold winters for you.

10:03.916 --> 10:05.625
You're gonna keep your
little paws in the desert,

10:05.708 --> 10:08.291
you're gonna chase little
bunny rabbits in the sand. Huh?

10:08.375 --> 10:10.250
There's no bunny rabbits in Arizona.

10:10.333 --> 10:12.500
They got snakes and scorpions.
She wouldn't last a week.

10:12.583 --> 10:14.333
You gotta shut the fuck up, okay?

10:14.416 --> 10:15.916
I'm just tryin' to have a moment here

10:16.000 --> 10:18.375
and apologize
for my absence to my baby girl.

10:18.458 --> 10:20.708
We're gonna go to Arizona, all right?

10:21.333 --> 10:23.583
I'm gonna drive a truck
and I'm never gonna let you go.

10:23.666 --> 10:25.500
I'll have one hand on the wheel
and the other hand on you.

10:25.583 --> 10:27.666
We'll put a little bed
right beside my chair.

10:27.750 --> 10:30.541
-Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

10:30.625 --> 10:31.583
Baby, you got the breath.

10:31.666 --> 10:32.875
Didn't I tell you to buy the Greenies?

10:32.958 --> 10:35.291
You didn't get her
the dog biscuits for her breath?

10:35.375 --> 10:37.333
Uh, I'm going inside.

10:38.833 --> 10:41.791
Hey, thank you
for my very own room.

11:50.000 --> 11:50.833
Yo!

11:54.541 --> 11:55.458
Henry!

11:56.250 --> 11:57.791
-What?
-You said I had my own room.

11:58.375 --> 12:01.458
Hawk, this is Spenser.
Spenser, this is Hawk.

12:01.541 --> 12:03.458
You two are gonna be roommates.

12:03.541 --> 12:06.125
Toilets are flushed at all times.

12:06.208 --> 12:07.583
Food is labelled.

12:07.666 --> 12:08.833
No fighting in the house

12:08.916 --> 12:11.833
and if there's going to be
any drinking, I instigate it.

12:11.916 --> 12:13.958
Now, I'd like you two
to get to know each other.

12:45.583 --> 12:49.291
There's my girl.

12:50.166 --> 12:51.250
Yes.

12:52.541 --> 12:55.083
You love Daddy. You love Daddy, don't you?

12:57.708 --> 13:01.416
Who's a big monster, huh? Who's a monster?

13:01.500 --> 13:02.875
Ooh.

13:03.458 --> 13:04.291
Give me my dog.

13:05.875 --> 13:08.208
Give me the dog. Come on.

13:12.916 --> 13:15.708
Come here, baby. Come here.

13:17.708 --> 13:21.416
There. You're gonna stay here
with Daddy. Okay?

13:25.458 --> 13:26.708
<i>Can you talk</i>
<i>to your daughter?</i>

13:26.791 --> 13:27.958
Put her on and I'll talk to her.

13:28.041 --> 13:28.875
<i>Hi, Daddy.</i>

13:28.958 --> 13:30.166
Hey! Hey, sweetheart.

13:30.250 --> 13:32.125
<i>Dad, I really need</i>
<i>your help with my report.</i>

13:32.208 --> 13:34.750
I was straight A's in English.
I'll help you with the paper.

13:34.833 --> 13:37.041
<i>That'd be awesome, Dad.</i>
<i>Are you gonna be home soon?</i>

13:37.125 --> 13:40.458
When I get there, I'll read what you have
so far and we'll talk about it.

13:40.541 --> 13:41.541
-Oh, sweetheart,

13:41.625 --> 13:43.416
hold on a second, I got another call.

13:43.916 --> 13:44.875
<i>Boylan, are you there?</i>

13:45.458 --> 13:46.291
I'm here, what's up?

13:46.916 --> 13:49.541
<i>He wants to meet everyone</i>
<i>at the bus yard ASAP.</i>

13:50.125 --> 13:53.166
-What the fuck is this all about?
- <i>Just be there.</i>

13:53.916 --> 13:55.333
All right.

13:56.125 --> 13:59.291
Sweetheart, yeah, listen,
I got a little bit of bad news.

13:59.375 --> 14:01.875
- <i>Dad--</i>
-No, it's not... It's nothing.

14:01.958 --> 14:04.666
I'm gonna be about 15, 20 minutes late.
I just got a call.

14:05.750 --> 14:07.333
<i>You know this report's a big deal.</i>

14:07.416 --> 14:08.666
<i>I need you to read it one more time.</i>

14:08.750 --> 14:10.500
Listen, the thing about the book,

14:11.208 --> 14:15.041
you've written all this beautiful stuff
about the darkness, about winter falling,

14:15.125 --> 14:18.958
about the darkness inside the place,
the darkness in Zenobia's heart.

14:19.041 --> 14:21.041
Just stay with that idea

14:21.125 --> 14:22.833
-and take it all the way through.
<i>-Really?</i>

14:22.916 --> 14:25.291
I think it's a beautiful idea.
I really do.

14:25.375 --> 14:27.458
-I think you should have confidence.
- <i>Uh-huh.</i>

14:27.541 --> 14:29.916
Now, I read the first draft
and I gave you some notes.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.333
But basically, what I'm tellin' you,
you turn that thing in,

14:32.416 --> 14:34.125
you probably get an A on the first draft.

14:34.208 --> 14:35.500
<i>But I know I'm not--</i>

14:46.833 --> 14:49.041
<i>-Dad, what happened? Dad?</i>

14:50.041 --> 14:51.125
<i>Dad!</i>

14:54.083 --> 14:56.041
- <i>Dad, what was that?</i>

14:57.500 --> 14:59.916
-Get the fuck off me! Get the fuck off!
<i>-Daddy!</i>

15:00.000 --> 15:02.083
-You know who you're dealing with?
<i>-Daddy!</i>

15:02.166 --> 15:04.916
You can't do this to a cop.

15:05.000 --> 15:06.750
<i>-Dad!</i>
-I'm a fuckin' cop.

15:08.041 --> 15:08.958
I'm a fuckin' cop.

15:12.291 --> 15:13.958
You talked
to the wrong people, asshole.

15:16.666 --> 15:18.041
I didn't give anything!

15:18.125 --> 15:19.916
I swear to God I didn't give anything!

15:20.000 --> 15:21.750
I didn't give a fuckin' thing.

15:22.333 --> 15:24.625
I didn't give 'em anything. I swear.

15:24.708 --> 15:26.333
Please, God.

16:00.416 --> 16:04.916
<i>Good mornin', Boston.</i>
<i>Welcome to April 18th.</i>

16:05.000 --> 16:08.083
<i>We're gonna have some picnic weather</i>
<i>today, can you believe that?</i>

16:08.166 --> 16:10.500
<i>With highs in the upper sixties.</i>

16:10.583 --> 16:12.250
<i>That's right, you heard me.</i>

16:12.333 --> 16:16.875
<i>Upper sixties and zero chance</i>
<i>of rain, so pack up the kids,</i>

16:16.958 --> 16:18.416
<i>pack up the sandwiches,</i>

16:18.500 --> 16:21.000
<i>and pour yourself some luscious lemonade,</i>

16:21.083 --> 16:24.000
<i>because it's spring time</i>
<i>in Boston, people.</i>

16:24.083 --> 16:26.708
<i>And have yourself a wonderful day.</i>

16:30.500 --> 16:33.250
<i>Next stop is Fifth Street,</i>
<i>in five minutes.</i>

17:03.166 --> 17:04.291
What the hell?

17:10.791 --> 17:11.791
Terry?

17:14.041 --> 17:15.041
Terrence?

17:16.375 --> 17:17.750
What happened to the...

17:27.458 --> 17:28.625
Terrence!

17:31.875 --> 17:33.791
Oh, my God!

17:33.875 --> 17:36.250
Oh, my God, somebody help me.

17:43.000 --> 17:44.416
Terrence!

17:45.208 --> 17:46.541
Terry!

17:51.375 --> 17:54.958
Are you fuckin' with me? Are you?

18:04.291 --> 18:06.916
Hey. He snores.

18:08.041 --> 18:09.041
What happened here?

18:09.125 --> 18:11.166
Oh, a little going away present.

18:11.250 --> 18:13.166
I got groceries for you.

18:13.791 --> 18:16.666
Don't eat anything on the right side
of the fridge. It belongs to Hawk.

18:16.750 --> 18:18.250
Aw, do you got any real food?

18:18.875 --> 18:21.166
Frankfurters are mine.
The rest is his.

18:21.250 --> 18:23.000
Where's the giant?

18:23.083 --> 18:25.333
Gets up at five, starts running.

18:25.416 --> 18:26.458
We got no milk.

18:26.541 --> 18:29.791
There's some oatmeal milk in there,
but it belongs to Hawk.

18:29.875 --> 18:31.583
Oat milk? What the fuck is that?

18:32.458 --> 18:35.416
Who knows? All I know is
he drinks it all the time.

18:36.458 --> 18:37.583
What? Do you have to put somethin' in it?

18:37.666 --> 18:38.625
