1:10:42.916 --> 1:10:44.083
Cat and the bell.

1:10:45.541 --> 1:10:48.583
Group of mice live very happily in a barn

1:10:48.666 --> 1:10:52.708
until, one day, a feral cat
starts eating the mice.

1:10:53.416 --> 1:10:54.958
<i>So, they all gather together one night</i>

1:10:55.041 --> 1:10:58.250
<i>to figure out what to do</i>
<i>about this feral cat.</i>

1:10:59.833 --> 1:11:01.083
So, one of the younger mice speaks up.

1:11:01.166 --> 1:11:02.333
- Fire!

1:11:02.416 --> 1:11:04.083
<i>"Why don't we place</i>
<i>a bell around his neck</i>

1:11:04.166 --> 1:11:06.125
<i>so that every time he's coming,</i>
<i>we can hear him?"</i>

1:11:06.708 --> 1:11:10.125
One of the older mice says,
"That is an excellent idea,

1:11:11.250 --> 1:11:15.416
but whom shall we get to place
the bell around the cat's neck?"

1:11:15.500 --> 1:11:16.750
Fire!

1:11:17.458 --> 1:11:18.666
So, what do we do, then?

1:11:20.583 --> 1:11:22.708
Sometimes you gotta just kill the cat.

1:12:01.458 --> 1:12:03.791
- I heard you just got out.
-Oh, man.

1:12:03.875 --> 1:12:06.416
Oh, I bet you could use
a good meal.

1:12:06.500 --> 1:12:09.125
Missed you, buddy.
Yeah, I need, uh, four burrito.

1:12:09.208 --> 1:12:10.208
Four burrito.

1:12:10.291 --> 1:12:12.250
-Uh, carne asada.
-Oh, you like that.

1:12:12.333 --> 1:12:15.541
And, uh, <i>pollo,</i> uh, <i>puerco.</i>
And you know what? Chorizo.

1:12:15.625 --> 1:12:17.625
Chorizo. You got it.

1:12:17.708 --> 1:12:18.916
<i>Puerco.</i> And you know what?

1:12:20.083 --> 1:12:22.375
<i>♪ I've had a lot of struggle</i>
<i>Burning up my tension ♪</i>

1:12:22.458 --> 1:12:23.666
<i>♪ So if you wanna make it count... ♪</i>

1:12:23.750 --> 1:12:26.500
-Uh... enchilada.
-An enchilada.

1:12:26.583 --> 1:12:29.625
-How's <i>mijo?</i>
-Oh, <i>mijo</i> is fine.

1:12:29.708 --> 1:12:32.583
I wasn't gonna ask you.
I haven't seen you in a while.

1:12:34.375 --> 1:12:36.208
- Yeah. Wife is good?
- Yeah. <i>Muy bien.</i>

1:12:36.291 --> 1:12:38.958
-What about, uh, quesadilla?

1:12:39.541 --> 1:12:43.000
Oh. If you want quesadilla,
just gotta wait on the tortilla.

1:12:45.708 --> 1:12:48.250
Quesadilla's...

1:12:49.708 --> 1:12:53.791
Oh, my wife Julia,
oh, she's so great.

1:12:53.875 --> 1:12:56.250
Yeah. She's great.

1:13:37.708 --> 1:13:39.125
No!

1:13:41.333 --> 1:13:42.166
Fuck!

1:13:50.458 --> 1:13:52.333
Yo! Get in!

1:13:58.208 --> 1:13:59.625
Oh, shit!

1:14:01.291 --> 1:14:02.791
-You're in big trouble.
-For what?

1:14:02.875 --> 1:14:04.958
You smashed the Riviera
through a restaurant!

1:14:05.041 --> 1:14:05.875
Get in the car!

1:14:05.958 --> 1:14:07.125
I'm tellin' Henry
you were driving the car.

1:14:16.166 --> 1:14:18.000
Man, you get beat up a lot.

1:14:18.083 --> 1:14:21.083
And I've noticed every single time
you get your face pushed in,

1:14:21.166 --> 1:14:23.375
you come back with just
a little bit more information.

1:14:23.458 --> 1:14:25.875
-Would you stop?
-I'm just saying.

1:14:25.958 --> 1:14:27.583
I don't think it's a very good tactic.

1:14:27.666 --> 1:14:28.708
They know who I am now.

1:14:28.791 --> 1:14:30.166
-No shit!
-They're gonna know where to find me.

1:14:30.250 --> 1:14:31.916
They're gonna
come looking for me at Henry's.

1:14:32.000 --> 1:14:33.708
They'll find Henry at Henry's.

1:14:34.791 --> 1:14:35.625
Shit!

1:14:42.708 --> 1:14:44.500
I hope you brought towels.
This isn't a Motel Six.

1:14:44.583 --> 1:14:46.458
Hey. We're here two days, four days max.

1:14:46.541 --> 1:14:49.666
It's not safe at Henry's.
Nobody's gonna look for us here.

1:14:50.250 --> 1:14:51.375
Who won't look for you here?

1:14:51.458 --> 1:14:53.708
Law enforcement. Trinitarios.

1:14:53.791 --> 1:14:55.583
Oh, the good guys and the bad guys.

1:14:55.666 --> 1:14:57.166
That makes me feel much better.

1:14:57.250 --> 1:14:59.125
It's also repetitive behavior.

1:15:00.125 --> 1:15:02.041
Hi.
Spenser.

1:15:02.125 --> 1:15:05.000
- Is this your house or a kennel?

1:15:05.083 --> 1:15:08.541
Both. I clean dogs,
I board dogs and I am--

1:15:08.625 --> 1:15:09.583
Come here.

1:15:09.666 --> 1:15:11.791
And I am very successful at it, all right?

1:15:11.875 --> 1:15:13.208
What did you expect? Punching bags?

1:15:13.291 --> 1:15:15.416
A bunch of grown men kicking
each other in the fuckin' neck?

1:15:15.500 --> 1:15:16.625
-Go to Henry's for that.
- Hey.

1:15:16.708 --> 1:15:19.333
-Leave my business out of it.
-I expected more from you.

1:15:19.416 --> 1:15:21.541
You're supposed to be his mentor.

1:15:21.625 --> 1:15:24.000
Create an atmosphere of
responsible thought and action.

1:15:24.083 --> 1:15:26.750
Instead, you got two grown men
runnin' around playing Batman.

1:15:26.833 --> 1:15:28.458
We're not playing Batman, okay?

1:15:28.541 --> 1:15:30.666
This is Batman business all the way.

1:15:30.750 --> 1:15:33.833
Got you and big boy over here
running through Boston all Robin-ed up.

1:15:33.916 --> 1:15:35.458
I am not Robin.

1:15:35.541 --> 1:15:37.125
And Alfred over here...

1:15:37.208 --> 1:15:38.958
Uh... Oh, Jesus.

1:15:39.041 --> 1:15:41.125
You are an enabling Alfred.

1:15:41.208 --> 1:15:43.333
You gave him the keys to the Batmobile.

1:15:43.416 --> 1:15:45.500
The Riv is not the Batmobile.

1:15:45.583 --> 1:15:47.291
Well, it serves the same purpose.

1:15:47.375 --> 1:15:49.083
Are we really gonna stay here?

1:15:49.166 --> 1:15:52.250
Because I'd rather take my chances
with the Trinitarios.

1:15:52.333 --> 1:15:53.625
At least they don't talk so much.

1:15:53.708 --> 1:15:56.583
No. Because they're too busy
trying to shoot you.

1:15:56.666 --> 1:15:58.833
You know, actually, they prefer machetes.

1:15:58.916 --> 1:16:00.916
Well, they're angry.

1:16:01.000 --> 1:16:04.291
Okay, well, I feel so much better now.

1:16:04.375 --> 1:16:05.500
So, I'm just gonna go.

1:16:05.583 --> 1:16:06.583
Let's go, boys.

1:16:06.666 --> 1:16:08.875
Snowball, Rosco, Smokey. Let's go.

1:16:19.375 --> 1:16:20.458
You hungry?

1:16:38.291 --> 1:16:39.458
Spenser?

1:16:52.916 --> 1:16:53.875
Did you call the police?

1:16:54.583 --> 1:16:55.750
No.

1:16:55.833 --> 1:16:58.708
And why would I? They probably did this.

1:17:15.625 --> 1:17:16.500
Hey.

1:17:18.125 --> 1:17:19.458
Are you a giant?

1:17:20.708 --> 1:17:21.750
Yeah.

1:17:21.833 --> 1:17:24.125
Are you a good one or a bad one?

1:17:24.208 --> 1:17:25.500
I'm a good one.

1:17:25.583 --> 1:17:27.958
Can you pull my bed over?

1:17:28.625 --> 1:17:30.291
I think I could handle that.

1:17:47.166 --> 1:17:49.250
I want you to put the pillow on the bed.

1:17:50.000 --> 1:17:51.125
Can you do that?

1:17:57.666 --> 1:17:58.916
Both pillows.

1:18:02.833 --> 1:18:05.541
Where would Terrence keep something
if he didn't want anybody to find it?

1:18:06.750 --> 1:18:07.625
I don't know.

1:18:08.416 --> 1:18:10.333
Well, do you have any idea
what they were looking for?

1:18:14.250 --> 1:18:15.083
What?

1:18:15.958 --> 1:18:17.750
Do you know what they were looking for?

1:18:18.333 --> 1:18:19.416
No, I don't.

1:18:26.083 --> 1:18:27.333
Why are you doing this?

1:18:28.958 --> 1:18:30.666
'Cause it's the right thing to do.

1:18:47.458 --> 1:18:48.791
Terrence...

1:18:50.291 --> 1:18:53.583
mailed this to me the day he died.

1:18:58.833 --> 1:19:00.041
It's a wire.

1:19:00.125 --> 1:19:01.375
I know what it is.

1:19:02.041 --> 1:19:03.375
Did you listen to it?

1:19:04.000 --> 1:19:04.916
I don't know how.

1:19:06.041 --> 1:19:07.000
I do.

1:19:28.416 --> 1:19:30.750
-You have some place you can stay?
-No.

1:19:31.916 --> 1:19:33.458
We're not goin' anywhere.

1:19:34.375 --> 1:19:36.333
I'm not getting chased out of my own home.

1:19:36.416 --> 1:19:37.708
Well, good for you.

1:19:39.125 --> 1:19:40.083
All right, look.

1:19:40.833 --> 1:19:42.791
I'm gonna call you
when I know something, okay?

1:19:44.291 --> 1:19:45.875
-Thank you.
- Okay.

1:19:46.750 --> 1:19:48.541
Can I hold on to this?

1:19:49.958 --> 1:19:51.833
It's got his handwriting on it.

1:19:51.916 --> 1:19:53.041
Of course.

1:19:54.041 --> 1:19:56.791
All right. I'll call you soon. Come on.

1:19:58.375 --> 1:19:59.666
<i>Come on, Boylan.</i>

1:19:59.750 --> 1:20:02.666
<i>We both want to get home</i>
<i>to our families. Help me out.</i>

1:20:02.750 --> 1:20:06.166
<i> You got no fuckin' idea</i>
<i>how deep this shit goes.</i>

1:20:06.250 --> 1:20:07.916
<i>So, tell me.</i>

1:20:08.000 --> 1:20:11.291
<i>Now, that information</i>
<i>is way above my pay grade, Mr. Altar Boy.</i>

1:20:11.375 --> 1:20:12.250
<i>But high up.</i>

1:20:13.291 --> 1:20:15.041
<i>High up.</i>

1:20:15.125 --> 1:20:18.250
All right, Los Oscuros is just
one seat at this fuckin' table.

1:20:18.333 --> 1:20:19.375
Oh, come on.

1:20:20.083 --> 1:20:21.333
The Feds.

1:20:21.916 --> 1:20:23.875
Give me something good
to whet their appetite.

1:20:23.958 --> 1:20:25.833
What are you guys using
the Trinitario drug money for?

1:20:25.916 --> 1:20:27.166
What do you think?

1:20:28.083 --> 1:20:29.708
It's our ticket into Wonderland.

1:20:30.208 --> 1:20:33.916
Permits, pay-offs, construction.
All that. Dirty cops.

1:20:34.000 --> 1:20:36.583
-Like you?
-Yeah, like me.

1:20:37.958 --> 1:20:40.125
Who's running this thing?
How does it work?

1:20:40.208 --> 1:20:42.125
Trinitarios are working for Bentwood.

1:20:43.250 --> 1:20:47.958
<i>Bentwood works for Macklin.</i>
<i>And they all work for Driscoll.</i>

1:20:49.000 --> 1:20:50.291
They already know this.

1:20:51.041 --> 1:20:52.750
I need something concrete, Boylan.

1:20:52.833 --> 1:20:54.583
Come on, man. I'm on your side.

1:20:56.666 --> 1:20:58.833
Let me help you get
the best deal out of this.

1:20:58.916 --> 1:21:00.750
<i>Tell me about the Pony Express.</i>

1:21:01.291 --> 1:21:02.750
<i>I'll make it clear.</i>

1:21:02.833 --> 1:21:07.458
<i>Trinitario street gang and Tracksuit</i>
<i>Charlie do the Pony Express once a week.</i>

1:21:07.541 --> 1:21:10.958
<i>You tell your fuckin' Feds</i>
<i>to picture the biggest shipment</i>

1:21:11.041 --> 1:21:14.625
of fentanyl and oxy that they can imagine.

1:21:15.208 --> 1:21:18.541
All right? And when they get that picture,
tell 'em to triple it.

1:21:19.125 --> 1:21:20.208
Where and when?

1:21:23.375 --> 1:21:25.958
I will tell you that once I get my deal.

1:21:29.375 --> 1:21:31.833
<i>Trinitarios are working for Bentwood.</i>

1:21:31.916 --> 1:21:33.333
I swear to God, I didn't give anything!

1:21:33.416 --> 1:21:34.541
You're a rat, Boylan.

1:21:34.625 --> 1:21:36.291
<i>Bentwood works for Macklin.</i>

1:21:36.375 --> 1:21:38.500
Bad things happen
to tattletales, don't they?

1:21:38.583 --> 1:21:40.875
<i>And they all work for Driscoll.</i>

1:21:40.958 --> 1:21:43.583
I didn't give them anything, I swear!

1:21:44.083 --> 1:21:46.208
This is my favorite part, you fuckin' rat.

1:21:47.083 --> 1:21:50.500
I see you got kara... Excuse me,
karate, after school today, right?

1:21:50.583 --> 1:21:51.416
Yes, sir.

1:21:51.500 --> 1:21:53.166
You gonna be able to get
yourself home from there?

1:21:53.250 --> 1:21:54.125
Yes.

1:21:54.833 --> 1:21:56.833
- I need you home by 5:00.
-Yes, sir.

1:21:56.916 --> 1:21:58.041
- No later.
-Yes.

1:21:58.125 --> 1:21:59.916
-5:00 p.m. What time you comin' home?
-5:00.

1:22:00.000 --> 1:22:02.458
Please don't be late.
Your mother's killing me about this, so...

1:22:08.708 --> 1:22:09.791
Stay right here.

1:22:18.458 --> 1:22:20.500
-Spenser.
- Hey.

1:22:20.583 --> 1:22:21.875
What are you, lost?

1:22:22.666 --> 1:22:24.333
Nah. Just happened
to be in the neighborhood.

1:22:26.208 --> 1:22:27.875
Okay. Okay.

1:22:31.708 --> 1:22:34.666
The fuck
you doin' here, Spenser?

1:22:38.500 --> 1:22:40.208
I know about Wonderland, brother.

1:22:41.625 --> 1:22:42.958
I know you're in deep.

1:22:50.333 --> 1:22:51.708
You got any proof, Spenser?

1:22:54.333 --> 1:22:56.458
Yeah. Too much.

1:23:00.500 --> 1:23:04.208
You know, the good cop
that I know, if he's still in--

1:23:08.333 --> 1:23:09.916
-All right.

1:23:10.541 --> 1:23:12.250
Tell you what,
I'm gonna give you

1:23:12.333 --> 1:23:15.000
one last chance
to come clean about Wonderland.

1:23:16.500 --> 1:23:19.791
Cut a deal with the Feds, tell them
the truth before more people get hurt.

1:23:20.375 --> 1:23:23.375
You do your time like a man, brother.

1:23:23.916 --> 1:23:24.875
Like I did.

1:23:28.708 --> 1:23:29.708
Be a hero for Josh.

1:23:38.708 --> 1:23:40.583
Get the fuck outta here.

1:23:44.875 --> 1:23:46.375
That's what I figured.

1:23:48.041 --> 1:23:51.000
You always were a hard-head. Just like me.

1:23:51.916 --> 1:23:54.166
-Bye, roommate.

1:24:06.666 --> 1:24:08.458
<i>Trinitarios</i>
<i>are working for Bentwood.</i>

1:24:09.791 --> 1:24:14.000
<i>Bentwood works for Macklin.</i>
<i>And they all work for Driscoll.</i>

1:24:14.916 --> 1:24:17.291
What are we gonna do?
We're gonna get this done?

1:24:17.375 --> 1:24:20.250
Agent Burton, just use the tape
to clear Terrence Graham's name.

1:24:20.333 --> 1:24:22.333
This tape? It's not enough.

1:24:22.416 --> 1:24:24.625
What are you talking about?
Even without the tape.

1:24:24.708 --> 1:24:26.416
The drugs are enough physical evidence

1:24:26.500 --> 1:24:28.083
for a RICO case against
the whole Wonderland crew!

1:24:28.166 --> 1:24:29.791
<i>...Trinitario drug money for?</i>

1:24:29.875 --> 1:24:30.708
<i>What do you think?</i>

1:24:30.791 --> 1:24:34.458
I'm sorry. I understand how you feel
but I can't tell you any more.

1:24:35.208 --> 1:24:37.375
Oh, my God. Now that's bullshit.

1:24:37.458 --> 1:24:39.916
You wanna help that cop's family?

1:24:40.000 --> 1:24:42.333
Walk away. We've got bigger fish to fry.

1:24:42.416 --> 1:24:44.291
We're the FBI. You push us,

1:24:44.375 --> 1:24:47.750
we will make so much crap
fly around for you and for Letitia,

1:24:47.833 --> 1:24:49.958
that you'll go back to Walpole.
And CPS will...

1:24:50.041 --> 1:24:51.916
<i>Let me help you get</i>
<i>the best deal out of this.</i>

1:24:52.000 --> 1:24:53.458
<i>Tell me about the Pony Express.</i>

1:24:54.041 --> 1:24:55.500
<i>I'll make it clear.</i>

1:24:55.583 --> 1:25:00.125
<i>It's Tracksuit Charlie, movin' drugs</i>
<i>with the Trinitarios every week.</i>

1:25:00.833 --> 1:25:02.666
<i>That's what the Pony Express is.</i>

1:25:03.208 --> 1:25:04.750
Hello, ladies.

1:25:04.833 --> 1:25:07.000
Lookin' more beautiful
than you did when you got here.

1:25:07.083 --> 1:25:08.875
There's someone here to see you.

1:25:08.958 --> 1:25:09.833
Who?

1:25:15.583 --> 1:25:17.375
No, no, no! Okay, Spense.

1:25:17.458 --> 1:25:19.125
Tell me about the Pony Express.

1:25:21.208 --> 1:25:23.833
Who's runnin' the drugs?
Gonna tell me what I wanna know?

1:25:25.333 --> 1:25:27.708
I wanna know everything.
Who's drivin'?

1:25:27.791 --> 1:25:30.625
What they're drivin'?
Where they're comin' from? When and where?

1:25:30.708 --> 1:25:32.458
You're going to tell me everything!

1:25:34.333 --> 1:25:36.291
Hey, man! They will cut your head off--

1:25:36.375 --> 1:25:38.166
- Oh, really?

1:25:38.250 --> 1:25:39.958
What are they driving, Charlie?

1:25:44.375 --> 1:25:47.208
Refrigeration van.
Coming from New Hampshire.

1:25:47.291 --> 1:25:49.541
Okay. It's coming down the pipes.

1:25:49.625 --> 1:25:51.333
It's hid in the refrigeration tanks.

1:25:51.416 --> 1:25:52.833
- <i>When?</i>
<i>-Tomorrow.</i>

1:25:52.916 --> 1:25:54.208
- <i>When?</i>
-<i> Today! Noon.</i>

1:25:54.291 --> 1:25:56.416
- <i>Which one?</i>

1:25:56.500 --> 1:25:58.458
<i>-What day do you meet, Charlie?</i>
- <i>Today!</i>

1:26:29.041 --> 1:26:30.458
Excuse me, sir. Are you okay?

1:26:31.041 --> 1:26:33.666
Oh, my God. You've got blood
all over you. Let me see?

1:26:38.000 --> 1:26:39.125
No.

1:26:47.250 --> 1:26:48.250
Oh, shit.

1:26:50.916 --> 1:26:52.583
-You forgot one in the back.
-I forgot one in the back?

1:26:52.666 --> 1:26:54.416
It's the driver's responsibility
to check the back.

1:26:54.500 --> 1:26:56.250
Who makes these rules?

1:26:56.333 --> 1:26:57.833
Hey. Hey! Hey!

1:27:03.000 --> 1:27:04.375
You motherfuckers is dead.

1:27:04.458 --> 1:27:05.833
Shit! Fuck.

1:27:05.916 --> 1:27:07.208
You... You dead.

1:27:08.291 --> 1:27:09.291
Yous is dead.

1:27:12.291 --> 1:27:13.291
Oh, shit.

1:27:18.291 --> 1:27:20.666
Every single one of them is full. Huh?

1:27:21.583 --> 1:27:24.041
This is how the cops are buying
their way into Wonderland.

1:27:24.125 --> 1:27:26.833
Jesus Christ! I haven't
done drugs in 20 years.

1:27:26.916 --> 1:27:28.333
I don't even know
what I'm lookin' at here.

1:27:28.416 --> 1:27:31.041
Fentanyl, oxy, coke.

1:27:31.125 --> 1:27:32.416
It's half the drugs in New England.

1:27:33.333 --> 1:27:34.791
Isn't this just gonna piss 'em off?

1:27:34.875 --> 1:27:38.000
Yeah, it's gonna piss 'em off once
they end up in federal prison, absolutely.

1:27:39.041 --> 1:27:40.083
Uh, I don't know if it's enough.

1:27:40.166 --> 1:27:41.833
You don't know if it's enough?

1:27:41.916 --> 1:27:43.250
What is wrong with you?

